# Cadence retro (2026-05-27) — retro-quality phase: convention, event-time, consistency

Cohort: etude-8hq.3 (define + require cadence retro-meta sidecars), etude-8hq.2
(add original event time to retro artifacts), etude-8hq.8 (repair + guard retro
subject consistency). Beads 3–5 of phase etude-8hq.

## Trigger
3-ticket cadence, flagged mechanically by `dogfood-completeness-audit.sh` check (c)
cadence-overdue. This is the FIRST post-cutoff cadence retro, so it carries a 7-key
retro-meta sidecar (the etude-8hq.3 convention) — dogfooding the very mechanism this
cohort built and proving check (f) passes on a compliant new cadence retro.

## What went well (preserve)
- **The multi-round plan gate earned its keep, repeatedly.** etude-8hq.3 took FOUR
  plan rounds, each catching a real, escalating defect: (r1) schema omitted the
  mandated `durable_changes` + WARN-only didn't satisfy "REQUIRE"; (r2) a
  date-granular cutoff was ambiguous against full timestamps; (r3) LEXICAL comparison
  of fractional-second ISO timestamps breaks at the boundary (`...00.000001Z` sorts
  before `...00Z`). etude-8hq.2 caught a 1-BLOCK/2-GO where codex was right (the log
  render hid capture time). None of these would have been caught by tests alone.
- **Adversarial seats that DRY-RAN the logic** (8hq.8: the planner + Opus both
  re-implemented the title parser over the live 17-ref corpus) caught a false-positive
  (`(2026-05-25/26)` → bogus `etude-26`) before it shipped. Empirical gate review >
  reasoned gate review.
- **Premise-check / not-a-vote-count (runbook P3, added in B17) paid off**: 8hq.2's
  lone verified-true BLOCK was adopted over a 2-GO majority.

## What went wrong / was caught late
- **The cutoff×supersede cross-bead interaction (8hq.8) was missed by the plan AND
  all three plan-gate seats** — caught only when the real `make dogfood-audit` ran on
  the actual re-captured ref. Superseding the pre-cutoff B16 minted a NEW ref with a
  post-cutoff `created`, which check (f) (from 8hq.3) hard-requires carry a sidecar →
  the sidecar-less supersede produced a hard GAP. The fixture tests + plan review all
  passed; only running the real mechanical gate on the real artifact surfaced it.
- **Timestamp-comparison footgun** (8hq.3 r3): lexical string comparison of ISO
  timestamps is unsafe with fractional seconds + RFC3339Nano trailing-zero trimming.
  Parse to instants.

## Root cause
Plan review and fixture tests reason about the bead's OWN new mechanism in isolation.
A bead that CREATES or MUTATES an artifact (backfill, supersede, re-capture) interacts
with ALL the OTHER active mechanical gates — and those interactions are invisible to
both fixture tests (which seed only the new check's inputs) and plan review (which
reasons about the new feature). The only thing that catches them is running the real,
composed gate on the real (or realistic) artifact.

## Durable changes landed
- etude-8hq.3: 7-key cadence retro-meta sidecar convention + check (f) (datetime-parse
  cutoff) + docs/retro.md.
- etude-8hq.2: optional `occurred_at` manifest field + `--occurred-at` + log EVENT
  column / effective-time sort (capture time never dropped).
- etude-8hq.8: check (g) subject-consistency guard + B16 annotation.
- THIS retro: a new "verify-the-verification for artifact-creating beads" note added to
  the review-gate runbook (run the real composed audit on the real artifact before
  declaring a data-repair/backfill/supersede plan sound).

## Decision
informational — process retro; the durable changes are implemented.
